article.headline: UC Irvine 67, Idaho 62 (OT)
article.story: MOSCOW, Idaho (AP) -- Greg Ethington scored five of his team-high 16 points in overtime as UC Irvine beat Idaho 67-62 Thursday. Jeff Gloger added 12 points for the Anteaters (13-11, 6-9 Big West). Gloger made a driving layup with 1:52 to play in overtime to give Irvine the lead for good at 63-62. Tanoris Shepard led Idaho (8-19, 6-10) with a career-high 28 points, all in the second half and overtime. Shepard made two free throws with 23 second left in regulation to knot the score at 54-54 and send the game to overtime. Earlier, Shepard scored 11 straight points, including three 3-pointers, in a span of 2:28 as Idaho erased an 11-point second-half Irvine lead. Shepard made his fourth 3-pointer with 3:42 to play to give Idaho its first lead of the game at 48-47. Nic Campbell scored 11 points and Ross Schraeder 10 for Irvine, which held Idaho scoreless for more than six minutes in a sloppy first half. Irvine did not score for more than 9:30 in the first half yet still led by four points at halftime. Idaho's leading scorer Dandrick Jones had 11 points for Idaho, six below his season average, and made 5 of 16 shots from the field.
